Author: timg
Content:
I'd pay 100$ for a really good one that describes one of my sites in a non-limiting way, and has ALL of the good qualities that a domain name should. I am just nearly certain that all of these that consist of any keywords that describe my sites are taken.

So, last night I registered for a similar service for 50$. But feeling guilty for spending money that I don't really have without exhausting every other option, I wrote a program to use letter/letter combination frequencies from a number of various data sets to find the best available names consisting of pseudo-words that are left.

It's man against computer, and this time I'm betting on the computer.
